be an option. &#10;Regular schools have several advantages however, the largest is exposure to other people which exists to a certain extent for homeschoolers but sometimes it is pitiful.  A similar issue is exposure to other ideas, never ever should homeschooling be done for ideological reasons, it is up to you to pass on your values to your children and up to then to evaluate the validity of them on their own with ALL the information. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="744" language="en" documentId="436" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="WillisBell" date="October 25, 2013 18:16" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://nanowrimo.org/forums/age-group-teens/threads/128227?page=3" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="436" notes="" title="Homeschooling - debate"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="321"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="322" end="744"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>